Implements the RISC operations.

Invoking a RISC operation in the multi-policy causes the same operation to be invoked in each of the sub-policies provided that the sub-policy is active and the input operands are valid. Each sub-policy maintains its own state. The register dictionary operations are inherited from BaseSemantics::Policy, which means that they apply only in the base policy (except set_register_dictionary() also calls the sub-policies. See NullSemantics::Policy for documentation of the RISC-like API.

Default constructor.

The default constructor initializes the multi-policy's register dictionary to be the same as the dictionary used by the first sub-policy. This can be changed by calling set_register_dictionary(), although that will set the dictionary for the multi-policy and all sub-policies.
